<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When reflecting from an existing file using Zend_CodeGenerator_Php_File::fromReflectedFileName(), the code that previously existed gets distorted, in that tab and newline characters are duplicated.</p>

<p>Original:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
if($foo)
{
    bar();
}
</code></pre>

<p>Becomes:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
if($foo)

{

        bar();

}
</code></pre>

<p>If Repeated becomes</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
if($foo)


{

            bar();


}
</code></pre>

<p>and so on...</p>

<p>Note however that new code (method) that is added is not affected by this, only the existing code gets mangled.</p>

